# kon Multi-Agent Workflow

## Plugin root (`KON_ROOT`)

Resolve **once** at the start of every kon command:

```bash
export KON_ROOT="$(python3 "$HOME/.kon/lib/_kon_paths.py" root)"
```

Resolution order (in `_kon_paths.py`): `KON_ROOT` env ‚Üí `~/.kon/config.json` ‚Üí kon clone ‚Üí `~/Desktop/kon`.

- Override anytime: `export KON_ROOT=/path/to/kon`
- Refresh config: `bash "$KON_ROOT/scripts/install_cursor_hooks.sh"` (from your clone)

All paths below use `$KON_ROOT/...`.

## Trigger

User invokes a **slash command** (kon extension system commands):

- `/kon:begin [goal]` ‚Äî interactive session; plain chat routed without `/kon:` prefix until `/kon:finish`
- `/kon:team <task>` ‚Äî full pipeline (explore ‚Üí plan ‚Üí milestone impl ‚Üí cleanup ‚Üí review)
- `/kon:design <task>` ‚Äî explore ‚Üí plan ‚Üí multi-agent design debate ‚Üí user confirms (no implementation)
- `/kon:quick <task>` ‚Äî skip explore/plan, lightweight review
- `/kon:debug <bug>` ‚Äî investigate root cause, propose fixes, user approves, then minimal fix
- `/kon:hunt <bug>` ‚Äî read-only bug analysis from source + best-effort repro SQL/tests (no fixes)
- `/kon:understand-codebase [scope]` ‚Äî PDF guide (concepts + architecture) + HTML flashcards/quiz
- `/kon:research <question>` ‚Äî external lookup (üìö Jun, writes `.kon/research.md`)
- `/kon:review` ‚Äî code review only (üìù Mio on uncommitted/staged diff)
- `/kon:review-pr` ‚Äî holistic PR review (üìù Mio: diff + body + comments + linked issues)
- `/kon:address-comments` ‚Äî triage PR review comments ‚Üí route to quick/team and implement
- `/kon:describe-issue <#>` ‚Äî summarize GitHub issue + comments (üìö Jun)
- `/kon:todo <task>` ‚Äî add a project todo (`.kon/todos.json`); manage in dashboard Todos tab
- `/kon:ask <question>` ‚Äî read-only Q&A (üé∏ Azusa explores, **no repo writes** ‚Äî session still tracked)
- `/kon:gc` or `/kon:gc <target>` ‚Äî garbage collect (dead code, comments, docs)
- `/kon:finish` ‚Äî mark current session completed
- `/kon:summarize` ‚Äî write session summary
- `/kon:retro` ‚Äî re-run session retro (optional; runs automatically after pipeline commands)

Append `--yolo` for autonomous mode: `/kon:team --yolo <task>`.

## How to run

### Interactive mode (`/kon:begin`)

For `/kon:begin`: read `$KON_ROOT/commands/begin.md` + `$KON_ROOT/skills/interactive-session/SKILL.md`.
Create one session; reuse its id for all plain-text follow-ups ‚Äî **never `init` again** until `/kon:finish`.

If the user message has **no** `/kon:` prefix and `kon_session.py active` prints an id ‚Üí treat as interactive follow-up (read interactive-session, route intent).

### `/kon:ask` / `/kon:hunt` ‚Äî read-only repo, session tracked

For `/kon:ask`: **create session JSON first**, then read `$KON_ROOT/commands/ask.md`. Spawn Azusa read-only only ‚Äî no code edits, no plan file, no mutating shell. Update session after Azusa. Do not read `teammate-flow`.

For `/kon:hunt`: same read-only rules as ask ‚Äî read `$KON_ROOT/commands/hunt.md` + `$KON_ROOT/skills/bug-hunt/SKILL.md`. Spawn Azusa with hunt output format; artifact `sessions/<id>/hunt.md`. Skip teammate-flow.

For `/kon:understand-codebase`: read `$KON_ROOT/commands/understand-codebase.md` + `$KON_ROOT/skills/understand-codebase/SKILL.md`. Azusa explore ‚Üí Jun author ‚Üí `build_understand_codebase.py`. Skip teammate-flow.

### `/kon:research` / `/kon:review` ‚Äî skip teammate-flow

For `/kon:research`: read `commands/research.md`, spawn Jun only.
For `/kon:review`: read `commands/review.md`, spawn Mio only (optional Mugi first with `--rubric`).
For `/kon:review-pr`: read `commands/review-pr.md`, spawn Mio only (review-pr mode).
For `/kon:describe-issue`: read `commands/describe-issue.md`, spawn Jun only (describe-issue mode).
For `/kon:address-comments`: read `commands/address-comments.md` ‚Äî orchestrator runs triage (steps 1‚Äì4); step 5 delegates to quick/team.

For `/kon:retro`: read `commands/retro.md` + `skills/session-retro/SKILL.md` ‚Äî orchestrator only.

For `/kon:todo`: read `commands/todo.md`, run `scripts/kon_todo.py` directly ‚Äî no agents, no session JSON.

### All commands (including ask)

1. **Session file (do this first, before anything else):**
   **For all other commands** ‚Äî first check for an open begin session:
   ```bash
   python3 $KON_ROOT/scripts/kon_session.py active
   ```
   If it prints an ID ‚Üí **reuse that ID** for `log-turn` / `complete-agent`. **Do not call `init`**
   (it refuses and would have superseded the begin session). Only `init` when `active` is empty.

   When `active` is empty:
   ```bash
   python3 $KON_ROOT/scripts/kon_session.py init --command "/kon:ask" --task "<question>"
   # other commands: --command "/kon:team" | "/kon:design" | "/kon:quick" | "/kon:debug" | "/kon:hunt" | "/kon:understand-codebase" | "/kon:gc" | ...
   ```
   Save the printed session ID. After each agent step:
   ```bash
   python3 $KON_ROOT/scripts/kon_session.py complete-agent --id <sid> --agent Azusa --summary "<one sentence>"
   python3 $KON_ROOT/scripts/kon_session.py wait-for-user --id <sid> --after plan --summary "<what user approves>"
   python3 $KON_ROOT/scripts/kon_session.py user-continued --id <sid> --summary "<user reply paraphrase>"
   python3 $KON_ROOT/scripts/kon_session.py finish --project .   # close open session (/kon:finish)
   ```
   Sessions live in `~/.kon/projects/<repo-name>/sessions/`. Path helper: `scripts/kon_session.py`.

### Workflow commands

2. Read the matching workflow file:
   - `/kon:begin` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/begin.md` + `$KON_ROOT/skills/interactive-session/SKILL.md`
   - `/kon:team` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/team.md`
   - `/kon:design` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/design.md` + `$KON_ROOT/skills/design-debate/SKILL.md`
   - `/kon:quick` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/quick.md`
   - `/kon:debug` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/debug.md`
   - `/kon:research` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/research.md`
   - `/kon:review` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/review.md`
   - `/kon:review-pr` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/review-pr.md`
   - `/kon:address-comments` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/address-comments.md`
   - `/kon:retro` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/retro.md`
   - `/kon:describe-issue` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/describe-issue.md`
   - `/kon:todo` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/todo.md`
   - `/kon:ask` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/ask.md`
   - `/kon:hunt` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/hunt.md` + `$KON_ROOT/skills/bug-hunt/SKILL.md`
   - `/kon:understand-codebase` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/understand-codebase.md` + `$KON_ROOT/skills/understand-codebase/SKILL.md`
   - `/kon:gc` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/gc.md`
   - `/kon:finish` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/finish.md`
   - `/kon:summarize` ‚Üí `$KON_ROOT/commands/summarize.md`

3. Read `$KON_ROOT/skills/teammate-flow/SKILL.md` for orchestration rules ‚Äî **skip for `/kon:ask`, `/kon:hunt`, `/kon:understand-codebase`, `/kon:research`, `/kon:review`, `/kon:review-pr`, `/kon:address-comments` (triage only), `/kon:retro`, and `/kon:describe-issue`**. For `/kon:debug`, follow `commands/debug.md`. For `/kon:design`, also read `$KON_ROOT/skills/design-debate/SKILL.md`. For external lookup in team/design, also read `$KON_ROOT/skills/external-research/SKILL.md`.

4. Spawn Task subagents. **Always pass `model`** ‚Äî same slug as the orchestrator (`get-orchestrator-model --id "$SID"`). See `$KON_ROOT/skills/model-inheritance/SKILL.md`. **Explore/plan agents** (Azusa, Mugi, Jun, design debate): new Task each time ‚Äî pass agent file (+ skill if needed).

   **Implementation loop** (Yui ‚Üí Sawako ‚Üí Mio per milestone): **spawn once per role per milestone**, then **`resume`** on fix/re-review until Mio approves. After **each** milestone Mio-approved, run **`wait-for-user --after milestone --milestone N`** and **STOP the turn**; then **`user-continued`** before next milestone or Nodoka/summarize. Full rules: `$KON_ROOT/skills/teammate-flow/SKILL.md`.

   | Step | Agent file (first spawn only) |
   |------|-------------------------------|
   | Explorer | `$KON_ROOT/agents/Azusa.md` |
   | Researcher | `$KON_ROOT/agents/Jun.md` + `$KON_ROOT/skills/external-research/SKILL.md` |
   | Design challenger | `$KON_ROOT/agents/Azusa-challenge.md` |
   | Planner | `$KON_ROOT/agents/Mugi.md` |
   | Implementer | `$KON_ROOT/agents/Yui.md` |
   | Cleaner | `$KON_ROOT/agents/Sawako.md` |
   | Reviewer | `$KON_ROOT/agents/Mio.md` + `$KON_ROOT/skills/strict-review/SKILL.md` |
   | Summarizer | `$KON_ROOT/agents/Nodoka.md` |

5. **Quality checks** ‚Äî Cursor `subagentStop` auto-validates Task subagent output via `on_subagent_stop.py`. Manual backstop (pipe each agent's full output):

   | Agent | `teammate_role` |
   |-------|-----------------|
   | üé∏ Azusa | `Azusa` |
   | üìö Jun | `Jun` |
   | üç∞ Mugi | `Mugi` |
   | üé∂ Yui | `Yui` |
   | üßπ Sawako | `Sawako` |
   | üìù Mio | `Mio` |
   | üìã Nodoka | `Nodoka` |
   | Design challenge | `Azusa-challenge` |
   | Design revise | `Mugi-revise` |

   ```bash
   echo '{"teammate_role":"Mio","teammate_output":"<output>"}' \
     | python3 $KON_ROOT/hooks/teammate_quality_check.py
   ```

   Block on `decision: block` or hook `followup_message`; retry the agent.

6. After Mio approves all milestones, spawn **üìã Nodoka** ‚Äî follow `$KON_ROOT/commands/summarize.md`, then run **retro** per `$KON_ROOT/skills/session-retro/SKILL.md` (user may skip).

7. Use `$KON_ROOT/skills/narration/SKILL.md` for üå∏ Ui narration beats.

8. Failure handling: `$KON_ROOT/skills/failure-handling/SKILL.md`.

9. Orchestrator context (anti-bloat): `$KON_ROOT/skills/orchestrator-context/SKILL.md` ‚Äî artifacts hold full output; route by file pointer only.

## Hard rule

**Never run `git commit` or `git push`.** Always present the commit message draft and wait for the user to run it.
